I’ve said it before and I’ll say it again…I absolutely love my job. I have set up my business to work in a way that works for me. I shoot certain days of the week because that works best for me, I start at a certain time because that works best for my schedule and everything that I do in my business fits into my lifestyle. It’s not fair to compare yourself to someone else when that could never be you to begin with. The comparison game is strong in this industry but it’s never been strong to me because I don’t allow it. If the goal is not moving me forward, I don’t want it. If it doesn’t make me happy, I don’t want it. If something goes wrong that I don’t like, I change it. The common denominator in success to me, is me. I control my business…and the person most in control of yours, is you. If you don’t like something, if you’re unhappy, if you’re feeling stuck, YOU have to make a change. I’m just here to have a good time and make people feel good about themselves. That’s what drives me every day. That’s the reason I get up every morning and put a bra on (sometimes 😂). But do what works for you, stay in your own lane and focus on yourself, things that are important to you and watch how things start to shift ❤️ Happy Monday friends!

Instead of sleeping on it, though, I just point people in the right direction, which is how to book a session with me. Fun little fact, I do not photograph models or do any free work unless I am personally doing a giveaway or mentoring another photographer. In that case, I will grab one of my past clients or a local lady from my VIP group and use them as a “model” in a teaching situation. Models are great for creative shoots or if you just want to practice a new skill, but None of the people that you see on my page are models, although they may look and feel like one after I’m done with them! There are a lot of other photographers that do styled shoots or creative shoots for themselves, but that’s just not me. So if you’re looking for free photos or to practice your modeling with a photographer, unfortunately, I will not be the right fit for you, but luckily, there are plenty of other photographers out there! Not only is doing your boudoir session scary, but then you have to see the photos and “hope” you love them! Some people are worried that they won’t look at the final images in a positive way. The poses feel so awkward when you’re doing them, so how can the photos possibly look good? Also, a lot of people worry they won’t see themself as beautiful or sexy when they’re looking at the photos. It’s so easy to complement somebody else and cheer on your friend or a stranger on the Internet, but when it comes to loving on yourself, and giving positive affirmations, it can be hard! But don’t worry, I am not guaranteeing that you are going to fall on the floor and love every single photo that I show you, but this is why I let you choose your favorites! You’re not going to hurt my feelings if there are some images that you don’t prefer, I just want you leaving with the ones that make you feel confident! I knew that you could do this and I’m happy when I prove to my clients that they too can be beautiful with boudoir photos too! Xoxo

I love a little teaching moment. Erotica is the type of photography where couple sessions are actually doing the deed. I photograph, what I consider intimate portraits. I pose you in a way that’s intentional, directional and implied. These are photos, not a video set. I pose you both, angle myself to where I feel the photo captures the moment and then we move onto the next pose. I know the photos LOOK sexy but that just means I did my job right 😂 I created an emotion and got a reaction from a photo. Simple as that. You’re not just making out in my studio and I am just there to photograph it. That would actually look a hot mess. Legs, hands, hair, and everything including light and positions all play a part in getting a great photo. I’m sure it’s exciting to THINK that having me there as a third wheel to witness the act gets you excited but I’m gonna pop your bubble real quick. It doesn’t even come close. Are we gonna have a good time? Yes. Could you possible get excited from being with your partner half naked? Yes. Will you act out those impulses in my studio? Absolutely not. I’m not opposed to those that do. There are some beautiful photos out there, but I get those questions a lot and I’m happy to answer them always! I also created a highlight bubble here in Instagram that explains couple sessions a little bit more so check that out and if you feel like I’m the right photographer for you, I would love to capture your photos for 2023 🖤

It’s my 7 year Boudoir Anniversary! Well, technically it was on the 10th but I’m finally finding time to share about it! 7 years ago I was asked to photograph a friend’s boudoir session and I reluctantly said yes. At the time I was a family/lifestyle and maternity photographer with no interest in getting into the boudoir side of things. Not because I didn’t like it but because it was so left field of what I was currently doing. I didn’t even know how to pronounce it let alone ask someone to model for me. I was a natural light, outdoor photographer so it was just not a good fit. Thankfully I said yes and we had the best time together! I loved the one on one aspect of it. I no longer had to chase after little kids or deal with husbands that didn’t want to be at the photo session. It just clicked for me. Doing what I love and making friends feel sexy? Sign me up. So I did just that. I drove so far up boudoir’s ass I was consumed! Literally 24/7 of learning, watching tutorials and building a business plan of what you see today. I literally haven’t stopped and still, on most days, have 100% excitement as day 1. I quickly learned that hustle culture is my thing and I thrive on being busy. I don’t like sitting still but I’ve learned to take time for myself. Making people feel good about themselves in turn makes me feel good. My client’s happiness is what drives me every day and that is what motivates me to work so hard. Everyone deserves to feel good about themselves, even if it’s just for the day. So, buckle up friends, 7 is my lucky number so this year HAS to be a good one! As a thank you here is another photo in my series of cell phone selfies and as always, only fans saw it first 😂 Thank you will never be enough but I’ll continue to say it THANK YOU a million times over for your support 🖤

Don’t let it happen to you 🖤 If you want someone that cares about your photos, wants you to have a good time and specializes in boudoir, that’s me! As I mentioned yesterday, when I first found boudoir I was also shooting everything else. As I learned more about it, I quickly realized that this had to be my specialty. It wasn’t just a service I was going to be able to offer along with everything else. It was too different, it was too unique and you really have to know what you’re doing when you are photographing someone’s boudoir experience. It’s everything from lighting, to posing, to making people feel comfortable in their underwear. It’s not something that everybody can do and it’s not something that everybody is great at. Over the years I have personally tried to master poses that work for all body types, because when I first started, I knew that I wanted everybody to look at my photos and know that they could do this. No matter the size, or age, or race, or gender, I wanted to build a business where everyone felt welcomed. It’s an investment but it’s an investment in yourself…and you can’t put a price on that ❤️
Even if you’ve been on the naughty list this year we still have room for you in January to update those nudes 💁🏽‍♀️ Want a spot? Karlamasonboudoir@gmail.com for more info 💋

Sharing your images is totally up to you! I never force anyone to share their images online unless they want to. At the end of the session, you make a final decision on how your images are shared online, if at all! The full release means you are OK with any of your images being online, this includes nudity/face. The partial release means sharing the images that are anonymous, without your face…think details shots and booty photos. Then, no release means no images online at all! I understand that some jobs don’t allow you to share or sometimes you just prefer to keep the images private, but at the end of the day, as long as you’re comfortable, I don’t care what you choose! But just know hot images travel fast, so choose wisely 😂 if at any point you do allow me to share your photos and then change your mind, I will gladly take them down whenever you want 🖤 would you share your images if you got them done by me?

We know that silly. Sometimes it’s hard to think of ourselves as beautiful or sexy, even if we are being told that by someone we love. “Of course they have to tell me that, because they are my ______.” No, they are telling you that because they see something in you that you don’t see. Other people don’t notice your “flaws” because we get to know you as a whole and view you in a positive way because you’re an amazing person. I’m the third wheel here. Most of the time I haven’t met you before or even know what you look like before you come over. I actually prefer it that way….because it doesn’t matter. We all have a beauty about us and I know I can find it in you. That’s why a lot of the time my clients say, “That doesn’t even look like me. WHO is that?” because you’re seeing yourself how I see you. I don’t care about your flaws or what you’ve been through in the past. I just see you for who you are in the short amount of time we have together. Everyone is beautiful in their own way and that’s why you see so many different and beautiful people on my page. I know how to find the parts of you you’ve never seen “like that” before. I know how to create beautiful photos that feature YOU because you have that beauty within you already. You just haven’t seen it through my eyes yet. So if you’re willing to let me, I’m willing to show you 💋 Who’s next?!

How many times have you stopped yourself from doing what you wanted because of the opinion of others? Probably a lot. We all do it. We worry about what others may think, when in reality, their opinion doesn’t matter. What do YOU want to do? Go do it! If you fail, oh well, at least you’ll learned something from it. But I’m sure there are so many times where you held yourself back and then regretted it later. Why? You could die tomorrow and you’re worried about what might possibly happen a week/month/year from now? Within reason and legally (😈) do whatever you want. There’s no right time and there could be no next time if you listen to close minded people. I meet SO many women that say, “I wish I had done this for myself sooner” because once you step out of your comfort zone you gain this new found confidence that you want to absorb over and over again. If you can come over to a strangers house and get half naked, the next scary thing doesn’t seem so bad! So push yourself this year to do something you’ve never done before and do it without asking the opinions of others 🖤

Allow me to introduce myself. I’m Karla of Karla Mason Photography. I’m the photographer, the educator of posing, social media manager, customer service representative, lingerie shopper, personal hype girl and confidence builder. I have built a luxury boudoir business in my home studio here in Stafford, Virginia which means you can show up and we take care of everything! From professional hair and makeup to lingerie, we have it all! 

5 fun things about me: 
1. I’m a Taurus in the best way
2. I’ll be honest with every opinion you ask of me. Not just what you “want” to hear 
3. You can tell me/say anything and it won’t shock/hurt my feelings 
4. Compliments don’t impress me. I already know, but I appreciate it.
5. Regardless, I’m gonna do what I’m gonna do
Bonus 6. I’m equally sour and sweet, like a sour patch kid. 

From day one I have wanted ALL women and couples to know they can come to my page and feel like they belong. Feeling good about yourself physically and mentally is for everybody and I show that through my photography. From the moment you walk in to the moment you leave with gorgeous photos, it’s all about you. No matter what you’ve been through or where this journey takes you, I promise to be your biggest supporter. If you’ve never had someone in your corner that fully supports you and will accept you without judgment, let me welcome you here. Come on over, physically and virtually to my home 💕 I promise to give you an experience that you’ll find rewarding and worth every penny. I want you to leave knowing you deserve good things and I hope that you feel empowered to go out and share that excitement with others because we all deserve to feel loved. Plenty of room here when you’re ready to be selfish and put yourself first. Will 2023 be your year to do that? I hope so 🖤 xoxo

We can’t let the New Year start without a good Sunday in the sheets! Just a classic, simple pose that feels awkward AF but beautiful in the after photo! Do you prefer the color or black-and-white?

1. Stretching is key! I know it’s not like a cardio workout but these poses can be a little tough especially because I’m asking you to hold them while I get the shot. Some photographers have you moving around constantly but I’m slow and controlled. Get ready to break a sweat like a yoga class would give you! 
2. Hydration is just self-explanatory. Makes your skin glow and helps with your sore muscles afterwards!
3. Eat something the morning of! Again it’s a mini workout so if you come on an empty stomach plus your nerves, you could feel woozy. I don’t need you passing out on me. I don’t give mouth to mouth (for free 🤓)
4. Clean, dry face and hair helps our hair and makeup artists get to work when you show up! Dirty hair does not hold better, they have professional products for that. So washing the night before or morning of is best!
5. Trust the process. You might feel a little shy but I’ll be doing it right along with you, making sure everything is perfect for your photos. You’ll hear me say, “Looks good, feels awkward”…because it’s true! But just trust you’ll get nothing but amazing photos if you just follow directions 🖤 What else do you want to know? Ask away…. And don’t worry, if you have booked a session with me already you have a full prep guide to help you prepare for your boudoir session! Let’s make 2023 amazing! Xoxo

This is not a side project. I use to do all types of photography like family, newborns, maternity, etc. Following the crowd, not knowing what it was like to really run a business. Yes it was fun for me and yes I loved photography but it wasn’t until I found boudoir that I really took this seriously. I was charging less and working more for literally nothing in return when it came to profit. I didn’t know how to run a profiting business but I knew I wanted one, so I did the work. I used all my free resources because at the time I didn’t have my own money. I was a stay at home mom to 2 kids…but 7 years later I’m helping to support us and helping other photographers do the same. I’m not shy when it comes to sharing how I do things or how I run my business, it’s not over complicated. It’s just working all day, every day and being consistent. Everyone wants to know how long it took me and how they can do it quickly but I don’t have an answer for that. It all depends on you. How hard are you willing to work to find the answers, make it happen and pay attention to the things that work and don’t work? How sensitive are you? How do you react to No and negative feedback? How long are you going to listen to the wrong people and let others option’s slow you down? I don’t sit there long or at all. You run your business, your business doesn’t run you, so the speed and level of your success doesn’t have a time frame. Don’t rush a good thing. Stop to pay attention to the little things…that’s what makes your business great. It’s not just one or two things, it’s ALL of it. Every move and thought you make determines your success and that all has to do with you 🖤

Happy International Women’s Day! It reminded me to think back to where I started 7 years ago….my first paying client. I vividly remember her telling me that my services were more than her wedding. I guess 7 years ago in a small town in Tennessee, that was the norm. But by then I had sat down to figure out how much I had to charge minimum per client to have a profiting business at the time, and it was still too much for some. But I loved her why on wanting a boudoir session, so I invited her to lunch to meet me and see my products and break the price down for her so that it was affordable for her budget through a payment plan. We clicked, she loved my why too and trusted me enough to book the session with me, without going down in price. I remember feeling so proud of myself for showing her that she was worth this experience, even if it was a little out of reach initially. It’s an investment in so many ways but most importantly to yourself. I’m proud of her for trusting herself and trusting me. I guess her reaching out years later for another session means something! But mostly I’m proud of myself for never giving up and trusting that I could do this and I am deserving of a business that not only helps women feel beautiful but that makes me feel good as well. Women can do amazing things and I promise to celebrate that, not just today but every day. The first photo you see is how I re-edited her photo today, the second photo is how I originally edited it 7 years ago and the third is where my old “studio” was…a tiny little dining room that I would swap into a boudoir studio. Never stop surprising yourself and never underestimate a woman! Xoxo

You don’t have to settle doing something you don’t love. I was a stay-at-home mom for over 10 years and while I loved it, I wanted more for myself. I didn’t like “asking” my husband if we had enough money to buy this or that. Or being told, “we don’t get paid for another week. You can’t get that”. I wanted to do more and provide more for my family so we didn’t have that financial stress. Money wasn’t the focus but let’s be honest, bills don’t get paid with thoughts and prayers. I was doing photography but I didn’t have a profiting business plan. I was doing what everyone else was doing so I never stood out and basically broke even. Finally I decided to do what I needed to do, put my blinders on and did the work. I made a plan that worked for me, put in the work every day, all day (probably a little too much) but it was something I wanted. Finding boudoir was my ah-ha moment. From the first session I knew this was what I was suppose to be doing and I never looked back. There are so many mental blocks that comes with being your own boss and running your own successful business and I can help. “Stay out the damn sun” ☀️🔫
Now, I know it’s summer time and I want you to live your best life (as you should) but please be careful of getting burnt and creating awkward tan lines. I’m not talking about the cute bathing suit tan lines, those are fine. I’m talking about the cross cross applesauce sports bra with 75 straps you decided to wear on your morning jog. The hand print sunburn where you forgot to rub in the sunscreen. Redness I can work with and calm it down, but crazy tan lines can’t be “fixed”. You CAN get a professional spray tan to even them out if that’s what you prefer but please for the love of all that’s holy and pure, do NOT use self tanners for your boudoir session. I will assume you want to look hot Cheeto dust orange with streaky hands and feet, ya’ll know what I’m talking about. Either come with your beautiful, natural skin or get a professional to bronze you up if that’s what you prefer! Preferably 2-3 days before your session. Need other prep work advise? I got you! Are you guilty of this? 

It’s so silly to try and compare yourself or your work to someone else. That’s just never been my thing. You don’t truly know how hard someone is working behind the scenes…or how slowly. For me, it was an all day, every day thing. I’d stay up til 2-3 am and be up again at 6am, just to get MORE work done while my kids slept. I also worked when they were awake. Creating information guides, tweaking my website, making giveaways/contests to draw more people to my page. It’s endless and there’s ALWAYS something to do. My way isn’t the right way, it was just the right way for me at the time. A lot of people give up quickly or get frustrated about things I don’t even give a second thought. You can only do what you can with the time you have and everyone’s time in a day looks different. Give yourself a break and do what YOU can and stop looking to other people that can utilize their time in a different way. Just because your business isn’t moving at a pace of someone else, doesn’t mean you’re doing it wrong 🖤 keep going

Feeling like I won every time I compete with myself…just trying to get better and better every day 🖤

Guess what happens every time I post. 

I lose followers. It never fails. Whether it’s a post or a reel, they just drop like flies. And you know what I do about it? Nothing. And you know how it makes me feel? I don’t care. And you know how it defines me as a photographer? It doesn’t. Because the numbers don’t matter. I’m no better or worse of a person whether my numbers change or not. You can’t “make” a person like your page and choose to stay. All you can do is use your platform as a place to display your best work and show people what it’s like to have you as their photographer. If they choose to stay or not is up to them, but don’t let it get you down! The right people always stick around if it’s meant to be 🖤 Just give them something to talk about…

When I was first asked to shoot a boudoir session I was nervous. I wasn’t even quite sure what boudoir was, so when I turned to Pinterest and google to snoop, my face was 🥴 Honestly it was cringe, cheesy and very “calendar-y” if you catch my drift. I didn’t even know the whole scope of different styles but I knew what I was looking at wasn’t for me. I was shooting everything else when it came to photography but I wasn’t a “look at the camera and smile” type of person. Costumes weren’t my jam, themes were not it for me and the idea of creating a new set every single time sounded like a terrible idea. I envy those that “NEED” to create something because my brain doesn’t work that way, but it’s nice to see! I wanted to show up with my camera and that’s it. I didn’t want to set up lights and backdrops and make it a 5 hour day. I was thinking, easy, breezy, beautiful cover girl. Show up to my simple space and let’s get some beautiful photos of YOU. Not hiding behind a prop, not dressing up as someone you aren’t…there are other photographers for that. I wanted to show off you in a space that was beautiful and neutral enough that fit along with everyone. I see a lot of you comparing yourselves to others or seeing other photographers “doing this and that” and feeling like you have to do the same. I never have. Y’all can have those elaborate set ups. You can have those costumes and themes that change monthly, but as for me I’m happy here. Don’t feel like you need to create something that isn’t for you. I’ve said no plenty of times because it just wasn’t my thing. Just because we are photographers doesn’t mean we photograph everything. Find something you love and be good at it…branch off and do something new if you want to, but don’t feel like you HAVE to be doing something else just because other people are ❤️
HMUA: @ido__artistry

Let go or be dragged. As this year comes to an end I hope you’re able to let go. Hanging on to something/someone that’s not there anymore will only drag you down. Let it go. Is it easy? Nope, but YOU need to take control back and move yourself forward instead of hanging onto the past. Stop waiting and hoping for what was, because the reality is, it’ll never be the same. It’s not there. Mistakes happen. Learn from them and move forward. It’s in the past for a reason so let it go and move on with YOUR life. Take the rest of this month to release that “what if” so you’re not dragging it into the new year. Let it go 🖤
